How the Model Works

Overview

The Prediction Method

The model predicts player points using a simple but effective approach:

Predicted Points = 0.5  (Last 5 Game Avg) + 0.5  (Last 10 Game Avg)

Why This Works

  1. Rolling averages smooth out noise - One bad or great game doesnt throw off predictions
  2. Recent form matters - The 5-game average captures if a player is hot or cold
  3. Baseline matters too - The 10-game average captures their typical output
  4. Simplicity wins - Complex models overfit; simple models generalize

The Betting Decision

Edge = Sportsbook Line - Our Prediction

If Edge >= 3 points AND odds >= -115 AND bet is UNDER:
     BET (confidence based on edge size)
Else:
     PASS

Why UNDERS Only?

The Explanation

Why UNDERS work: - When a player has a high line, it often means theyve been scoring well recently - The models rolling average predicts regression - theyll likely score closer to their norm - Betting UNDER captures this regression

Why OVERS fail: - When a player has a low line, betting over requires them to exceed expectations - The model isnt good at predicting when players will break out - Sportsbooks price overs more accurately

The Vig Problem

Why Most Betting Loses

Player prop odds are NOT -110 (the standard). They average -135 to -170.

Bet Type Average Odds % Worse than -110
Over -132 57%
Under -138 60%

What This Means

At -135 average odds, you need to win 57.4% just to break even.

The model wins 58-62% of bets, but thats barely above break-even for these odds.

Solution: Only bet when you find odds of -115 or better through line shopping.

Confidence Levels Explained

How We Define Confidence

Level Edge Odds Historical ROI Why
HIGH 4+ pts >= -115 +6.7% Large edge overcomes vig
MEDIUM 3-4 pts >= -115 +2.5% Moderate edge, still profitable
LOW 2-3 pts >= -115 ~0% Edge too small for vig
AVOID Any < -115 OR Over -7% to -12% Vig eats all profit

The Math Behind It

At -115 odds: - Break-even win rate: 53.5% - Model wins at edges: - 4+ pts: 51.4% (profitable because better odds) - 3+ pts: 50.8% (marginally profitable) - 2+ pts: 49.5% (break-even)

Key insight: We dont need to win more than 50% if were getting plus odds or low vig. Line shopping moves us from -135 average to -105/-115, dramatically changing the math.

Quick Reference

The Rules

Rule Requirement Why
Bet Type UNDERS ONLY Model predicts regression, not breakouts
Edge 3+ points Smaller edges dont overcome vig
Odds -115 or better Worse odds = losing money
Confidence HIGH or MEDIUM LOW/AVOID = break-even or worse

What NOT To Do

  • Never bet OVERS - They lose 10%+ ROI historically
  • Never bet bad odds - Anything worse than -115 eats your profit
  • Never bet small edges - Under 3 points isnt worth the risk
  • Never bet everything - Be selective, not comprehensive
